Mitchell House hosted its annual golf day at the Polokwane Golf Club last Thursday with 52 players taking part in a competition in Individual Stableford format.
The winner was Pierre Bloem with 44 points, followed by Imtyaaz Mohamed with 40. Emmanuel Runyowa was nearest to the pin on the 11th with Mohamed also claiming the longest drive on the 2nd. Bloem was nearest to the pin on the 16th.
Story and photos: BARRY VILJOEN
